subject: rlh54dvjgfm
comments: I found that it was more fun to pick the risky option as it would switch up the number of options more frequently and it made it feel like more of a game.

subject: nw06shun0sq
comments: I think that I took more risks when all outcomes were decreases. I think that it was very spilt between the two though, I like taking risks. The reason I would stop taking risks is when the outcomes did not work in my favor more times in a row.

subject: r31oari8p6
comments: I preferred to go with the risky option when the numbers were green, and I tended to go with the safe option when the numbers were red. After a few trials, the average difficulty was not that hard so I preferred to not risk adding a large number and I tried to keep closer to 32 when possible, and didn't care as much if I risk taking none away.

subject: u652vhnjbm
comments: I preferred picking risky ones when they were green, indicating fewer color blocks as opposed to risky red decks. I felt immediate relief when I rarely chose the risky decks that were red but that resulted in 0 change, but also felt excitement when I picked risky green ones that doubled the reduction.

comments: I didn't have a preference but being colorblind made this difficult.
